CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 20, 1959, pg. A14 reads: "The M.R.S. Club - A group of young matrons, organized recently, have set their values high in field of charity and have, so far, aided the Aged Ministers and Laymen's Home on Oakwood St. Left to right are Mmes. Mildred Wallace, Delora Anderson, Valerie Rodgers, president; Yvonne Griggs, Penelope Calloway, treasurer.  Seated: Mmes. Adrienne Brooks, secretary, and Jeanette Carter.  The group has planned a bake sale, with proceeds aimed at helping some institution. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of M.R.S. Club members, seated, from left: Adrienne Brooks and Jeanette Carter; standing: Mildred Wallace, Delora Anderson, Valerie Rodgers, Yvonne Griggs, and Penelope Calloway, posed in interior with small bar, another version
